          "title": "Warmup: General - World Gym",
          "notes": "Push–Pull @ World Gym — Power Week — Pull B\n\nFlow: muscle-up power → skill pair (archer + back lever) → Nordic → commercial cable hypertrophy block.\n\nGeneral warm-up (~7 min, log as duration):\nFace Pull (Cable) 1×10; Cable External Rotation 1×10/side light; Seated Cable Row – Bar Grip 1×10 light; Face Pull 1×10 (ER emphasis); Light lat pulldown 1×10; band pull-apart 1×10 if you brought a band, else light cable row 1×10; bodyweight squat 1×10.\n\nPower: muscle-up is the first heavy slot—warm up with singles or easier variations; rest 3–4 min on work sets.\n\nSee programs/khoiphan21/push-pull-world-gym for progression and week-type rules.",
